The paper discusses the use of predictive algorithms and statistical information for online decision-making, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new technique called compensated coupling, which is a probabilistic method used in probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses online packing and matching problems, which fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT).
